article.headline: Marist 55, Bucknell 40
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Ryan Stilphen led all scorers with 10 points as Marist capitalized on 18 turnovers in a 55-40 win over Bucknell on Wednesday. Ben Farmer added nine points and Ryan Schneider and David Devezin each had eight for Marist (4-3.) Justin Castleberry led Bucknell (2-3) with nine points, but was also one of three Bison players with three turnovers. Marist shot 46 percent in the first half and took a 29-17 lead at the break. Poor shooting plagued Bucknell. The Bison managed just 21 percent from the field in the first and shot 32 percent for the game. John Griffin had seven points and six rebounds for Bucknell.
